# General rules

- Read `AGENTS.md` once per session before doing meaningful work.
- English only in repo content (code, docs, commit messages, PR titles). Chat with the human team can be in any language.
- Prefer editing existing files over creating new ones.
- Never disable typecheck or lint to make a change land. Fix the root cause.
- Never add `Co-Authored-By: Claude` or any AI-attribution trailer to commits or PRs.
- No comments that restate code. Only document the *why* when it is non-obvious.
- One logical change per commit. No combo commits.
- When making a load-bearing decision without an existing spec, draft an ADR in `ai-logs/decisions/` in the same PR.
